        </p>

        <h3>What type of cookies does WSO2 AD 4.5.1 use?</h3>
        <p>
            WSO2 AD 4.5.1 uses persistent cookies and session cookies. A persistent cookie helps WSO2 AD 4.5.1 to
            recognize you as an existing user so that it is easier to return to WSO2 or interact with WSO2 AD 4.5.1
            without signing in again. After you sign in, a persistent cookie stays in your browser and will be read by
            WSO2 AD 4.5.1 when you return to WSO2 AD 4.5.1.
        </p>
        <p>
            A session cookie is a cookie that is erased when the user closes the web browser. The session cookie is
            stored in temporary memory and is not retained after the browser is closed. Session cookies do not collect
            information from the user's computer.
        </p>

